{"type":"step-attempt","step":"code-review","sessionId":"12afc02c-acc5-4f05-b11e-ff1bd68d1047","outcome":{"verdict":"approved","findingsPath":"specrunner/changes/verdict-fidelity-and-fixer-noop/review-feedback-001.md","error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"approved":true,"findings":[{"severity":"medium","resolution":"fixable","file":"src/core/step/__tests__/judge-verdict.test.ts","title":"TC-021 (must) — executor judgeVerdictFn dispatch not directly unit-tested","rationale":"test-cases.md TC-021 requires a unit test that runs through executor.finalizeStep with a JudgeReportResult bearing a medium-severity fixable finding for both a regression-gate step (with judgeVerdictFn set) and a spec-review step (without), verifying that each yields a different verdict. Current coverage uses (a) pure function unit tests for deriveRegressionGateVerdict/deriveJudgeVerdict, (b) TC-020 function reference test, (c) TC-RG-01 e2e test which only uses high/fixable and does not distinguish the two dispatch paths. The dispatch logic is a trivial one-liner conditional so implementation risk is low; marking Fix: no as non-blocking."}],"observations":[{"severity":"low","file":"src/core/step/executor.ts","title":"no-op override applies even when toolResult.status is 'error'","rationale":"detectNoOp fires when completionReason==='success' and no source files changed, then the verdictOverride replaces whatever finalizeStep derived — including 'error' from toolResult.status='error'. In practice this is benign (both 'error' and 'needs-fix' send the job through the fix loop), but the behaviour differs from the design doc which scopes no-op detection to 'approved'/'success' outcomes. Not blocking."}]},"followUpAttempts":1,"transientRetryAttempts":0},"startedAt":"2026-07-03T13:27:04.865Z","endedAt":"2026-07-03T13:33:26.242Z"}
