{"type":"step-attempt","step":"regression-gate","sessionId":"d134cd54-210b-4dea-b61f-f0c76712aa51","outcome":{"verdict":"needs-fix","findingsPath":"specrunner/changes/verdict-fidelity-and-fixer-noop/regression-gate-result-001.md","error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"approved":false,"findings":[{"severity":"high","resolution":"fixable","file":"src/core/step/executor.ts","title":"verdictOverride still unconditionally overrides producer `status:error` — fix not applied","rationale":"The ledger claimed this was fixed, but executor.ts was only touched by the implementer commit (a36daf336) and not by the code-fixer (8aff2d389). The guard `&& verdict !== 'error'` is absent: `if (agentResult?.verdictOverride !== undefined) { verdict = agentResult.verdictOverride; }` remains unconditional. When code-fixer completes with completionReason=success, calls report_result({status:'error'}), and detectNoOp fires (no source files changed), verdictOverride='needs-fix' overrides verdict='error'. The cross-boundary-invariants reviewer identified this and proposed the one-line fix: add `&& verdict !== 'error'` to the condition.","line":853}],"observations":[{"severity":"low","file":"src/core/step/__tests__/judge-verdict.test.ts","title":"TC-021 executor judgeVerdictFn dispatch — verified fixed","rationale":"The TC-021 test block was added by code-fixer commit 8aff2d389. Two tests call executor.execute() with a JudgeReportResult bearing a medium-severity fixable finding: regression-gate step (judgeVerdictFn=deriveRegressionGateVerdict) → needs-fix, spec-review step (no judgeVerdictFn) → approved. Both dispatch paths are directly exercised. Finding 1 is confirmed fixed."}]},"followUpAttempts":0,"transientRetryAttempts":0},"startedAt":"2026-07-03T13:45:09.947Z","endedAt":"2026-07-03T13:52:09.276Z"}
